                            <comment id="13097584" author="aloubyansky" created="Wed, 12 Aug 2015 07:34:01 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;The bodies of if-else and try-catch-finally are batches, i.e. each body will be translated into a composite operation.&lt;br/&gt;
When the CLI is in the batch mode, it doesn&apos;t execute entered operation requests but adds them to the batch until run-batch command is invoked. Commands that don&apos;t support batch mode are executed immediately outside the currently active batch (this is done support ls, cd and other commands).&lt;br/&gt;
reload and shutdown commands do not support batch mode because they need to perform some logic besides sending an operation request. So, in this case, :shutdown(restart=true) should have been used instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Or the bodies of control flow blocks should not be batches.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13110432" author="aloubyansky" created="Fri, 18 Sep 2015 09:23:39 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;If-else and try-catch-finally are not starting batches implicitly any more.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
